": \"correctness\",\n      \"claim\": \"CalculatorFacade compute method can delegate power operations to Calculator.power\",\n      \"grounding\": [\n        {\n          \"quote\": \"public int compute(String op, int a, int b) { ... }\",\n          \"source\": \"signature:CalculatorFacade.compute\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"quote\": \"public int power(int base, int exponent) { ... }\",\n          \"source\": \"signature:Calculator.power\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"quote\": \"import com.example.core.Calculator;\",\n          \"source\": \"edge:api->core imports\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"test\": \"import com.example.core.Calculator;\\nimport com.example.api.CalculatorFacade;\\n\\nit('CalculatorFacade compute can handle power operations', () -> {\\n  CalculatorFacade facade = new CalculatorFacade();\\n  // Assuming compute method supports \\\"power\\\" operation\\n  int result = facade.compute(\\\"power\\\", 2, 3);\\n  assertEquals(8, result);\\n})\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"c4\",\n      \"concern\": \"security\",\n      \"claim\": \"Calculator.power input validation prevents integer overflow exploitation through large exponents\",\n      \"grounding\": [\n        {\n          \"quote\": \"public int power(int base, int exponent) { ... }\",\n          \"source\": \"signature:Calculator.power\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"quote\": \"Calculator.power(2, -1) throws IllegalArgumentException with message containing 'negative'\",\n          \"source\": \"acceptance criteria\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"test\": \"import com.example.core.Calculator;\\n\\nit('Calculator.power prevents potential overflow with large exponents', () -> {\\n  Calculator calc = new Calculator();\\n  // Test with potentially problematic large exponent\\n  assertDoesNotThrow(() -> {\\n    int result = calc.power(2, 30); // 2^30 = 1073741824, within int range\\n    assertTrue(result > 0);\\n  });\\n})\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```",
